{"lemma":"أُنْسُ","slug":"أُنْسُ","root":"#.ن.س","root_slug":"_-ن-س","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ن-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أُنْسُ","root":"أنس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":18},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n1335","n1336","n1338"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D9%86%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feel safe and at ease near someone"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to solace, to console, to tranquil, to render easy, to delight"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be friendly or sociable towards, to keep company"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feel, to be sensible of, to perceive, to experience, to hear or see"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1335","headword_ar":"اُنْسٌ","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sociableness; companionableness; conversableness; inclination to company"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"converse; friendliness; amicableness; socialness; familiarity: cheerfulness; gayness; gladsomeness: contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$apN","text_ar":"وَحْشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, A, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joy; gladness; happiness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 652:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity, of heart, and freedom from shrinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from aversion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) an inf. n. of 1, (S, M,) as are also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasN","text_ar":"اَنَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasapN","text_ar":"اَنَسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) but this is rare as signifying the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$apN","text_ar":"وَحْشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anisa bihi","text_ar":"اَنِسَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unusN","text_ar":"اُنُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not: (AZ, AHát, Msb, TA:) this latter is a subst. from that verb [signifying as explained above]: (Msb:) or only signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"converse, and companionship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"familiarity, with women;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, AHát, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"amatory conversation and conduct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"talk of young men and young women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) [but of all the forms above,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unosN","text_ar":"اُنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that which is most commonly used, at least in post-classical works, as signifying the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waHo$apN","text_ar":"وَحْشَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Delight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of delight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing that gives delight."},{"kind":"text","text":"] A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA saAkiniY mak~apa laA zilotumu\n                      \n                     \n                        A^unosFA lanaA A_in~iYa lamo A^anosakumo\n                      \n                     \n                        maA fiykumu EayobN siwaY qawolikumo\n                      \n                     \n                        Einoda All~iqaA A^awoHa$anaA A^unosukumo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O inhabitants of Mekkeh, may ye not cease to be a delight to us: verily I have not forgotten you: there is in you no fault beside your saying, at meeting, Your sociableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companiableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has made us feel lonely and sad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, in your absence]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wH$","text_ar":"وحش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoHa$a","text_ar":"اَوْحَشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". But this signification, though allowable as tropical, is perhaps post-classical.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A^unos","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اُنْس"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A@bonu A^unosi fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ ا@بْنُ اُنْسِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa A@bonu A^unosika","text_ar":"كَيْفَ ا@بْنُ اُنْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa taraY A@bona A^unosika","text_ar":"كَيْفَ تَرَى ا@بْنَ اُنْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["T","S","A","K","M","Msb","TA","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n1336","headword_ar":"اـِنْسٌ","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unosN","text_ar":"اُنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chosen, select, particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special, friend"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A_inosK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اـِنْسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A^unosK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ اُنْسٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (So in a copy of the A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A_inosiY","text_ar":"هٰذَا اـِنْسِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosuka","text_ar":"اـِنْسُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonu A_inosika","text_ar":"ا@بْنُ اـِنْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is my chosen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular, friend;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy chosen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular, friend."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonu A_inosi fulaAnK","text_ar":"ا@بْنُ اـِنْسِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flAn","text_ar":"فلان"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Abn A^unosi","text_ar":"ابن اُنْسِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":114},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the chosen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"particular, friend of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) One also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa","text_ar":"كَيْفَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@bonu A_inosika","text_ar":"ا@بْنُ اـِنْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unosika","text_ar":"اُنْسِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa taray A@bona","text_ar":"كَيْفَ تَرَي ا@بْنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosika","text_ar":"اـِنْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, Fr, A) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unosika","text_ar":"اُنْسِكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) meaning himself, (AZ, Fr, S, S TA,) i. e., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How dost thou regard me in my companionship with thee?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or the meaning is, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how dost thou find thyself?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how is thyself?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mankind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposite of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jin~N","text_ar":"جِنٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasN","text_ar":"اَنَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Akh, S, TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) the last being a gen. n., (Msb,) but applied to the male (S, * Msb) and female, (S, Msb, K,) and sing. and pl.: (Msb:) one is [also] termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosiY~N","text_ar":"اـِنْسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasiY~N","text_ar":"اَنَسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) the former of which is a rel. n. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) [and the latter, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasN","text_ar":"اَنَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the fem. of each is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":":] the vulgar apply to a woman, instead of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is the more approved,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnapN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) this latter [accord. to some] should not be used: (S:) but it is correct, though rare: it is said in the K to occur in poetry, but supposed to be post-classical: it occurs, however, in classical poetry, and has been transmitted by several authors: (MF:) the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, TA) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=naAsN","text_ar":"ا=نَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, TA;) and (of the same, K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nws","text_ar":"نوس"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", M)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unaAsN","text_ar":"اُنَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K ubi suprà,) with which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsN","text_ar":"نَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn., (S, M, Msb, K,) being a contraction thereof; (Sb, S, M, Msb;) and (of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosiY~N","text_ar":"اـِنْسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, M, or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasiY~N","text_ar":"اَنَسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", Lh, S, M, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAsiY~N","text_ar":"اَنَاسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, S, M, Msb, K,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karaAsiY~u","text_ar":"كَرَاسِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kurosiY~N","text_ar":"كُرْسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraAHynu","text_ar":"سَرَاحينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sirHaAnN","text_ar":"سِرحَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) after the same manner as they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAnK","text_ar":"اَرَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAnibu","text_ar":"اَرَانِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr, TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAsK","text_ar":"اَنَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, M,) in the accus. case"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAsiYa","text_ar":"اَنَاسِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the word is read in the Kur xxv. 51, by Ks, (TA,) and by Yahyà Ibn-El-Hárith, (K, TA,) dropping the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"between the second and last radical letters, [for, with some others, it seems, they held the word to be derived from the root"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nsY","text_ar":"نسى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAsiyapN","text_ar":"اَنَاسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) in which the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a substitute for one of the two yás in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAsiY~u","text_ar":"اَنَاسِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to Mbr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaAsiyapN","text_ar":"اَنَاسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosiY~N","text_ar":"اـِنْسِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the TA, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosiy~apN","text_ar":"اـِنْسِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which I regard as a mistranscription,] and is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanaAdaqapN","text_ar":"زَنَادَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zanaAdiyqu","text_ar":"زَنَادِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAzitapN","text_ar":"فَرَازِتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraAziynu","text_ar":"فَرَازِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) and you say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosay~uwna","text_ar":"اـِنْسَيُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsN","text_ar":"نَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is masc., as in the Kur ii. 19, &c.; and sometimes fem., as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tribe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a body of men,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiylapN","text_ar":"قَبِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^ifapN","text_ar":"طَايِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the phrase, mentioned by Th,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='atoaka Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتَْكَ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tribe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of people"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiToEap","text_ar":"قِطْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"came to thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuwAlA_inosaAni","text_ar":"بَنُوالاـِنْسَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sons of Adam."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"النَّاسُ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", an expression mentioned by Sb, means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Men in every place and in every state are men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"bilaAdN bahaA kun~aA wakun~aA nuHib~uhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        A_i*i Aln~aAsu naAsN waAlbilaAdu bilaAdu"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A country in which we were, and which we used to love,] since the men were ingenuous men, and the country was a fruitful country."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) The following trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo A^aTaAEa A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"لَوْ اَطَاعَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsa fiY Aln~aAsi lamo yakuno naAsN","text_ar":"النَّاسَ فِى النَّاسِ لَمْ يَكُنْ نَاسٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If God complied with the prayer of men with respect to men there would be no men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to mean, that men love to have male children born to them, and not females, and if there were no females, or if the females were not, men would cease to be. (TA.) It is related that a party of the jinn, or genii, came to a company of men, and asked permission to go in to them, whereupon the latter said to them, Who are ye? and they answered,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsN mina","text_ar":"نَاسٌ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljn~i","text_ar":"الجنِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people of the jinn"},{"kind":"text","text":"], making their answer to accord. with common usage; for it is customary for men, when it is said to them, Who are ye? to answer,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsN mino baniY fulaAnK","text_ar":"نَاسٌ مِنْ بَنِى فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Men of the sons of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IJ, M, L: but in the L, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nAs","text_ar":"ناس"},{"kind":"text","text":", in both instances, we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unaAsN","text_ar":"اُنَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAsN","text_ar":"نَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nws","text_ar":"نوس"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Respecting the derivation of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAnN","text_ar":"اـِنْسَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", authors differ, though they agree that the final"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is augmentative: the Basrees say that it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_inosu","text_ar":"الاـِنْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and its measure is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolaAnN","text_ar":"فِعْلَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) but an addition, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", is made in its dim., [which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unayosiyaAnN","text_ar":"اُنَيْسِيَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like as an addition is made in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwayojilN","text_ar":"رُوَيْجِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [but it should be observed that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwayojilN","text_ar":"رُوَيْجِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more probably the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAjilN","text_ar":"رَاجِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] some say that it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iynaAsN","text_ar":"اـِينَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “perception,” or “sight,” and “knowledge,” and “sensation;” because man uses these faculties: (TA:) and Mohammad Ibn-'Arafeh El-Wásitee says that men are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_insiy~uwni","text_ar":"اـِنسِيُّونِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because they are seen ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuw^onasuwna","text_ar":"يُوْنَسُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","M","AZ","Fr","Akh","TA","Msb","MF","Lh"]},{"entry_id":"n1338","headword_ar":"اَنَسٌ","root":"Ans","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unosN","text_ar":"اُنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (S, K.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (Akh, S, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A numerous company of men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tribe"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~u","text_ar":"حَىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"staying, residing, dwelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abiding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people of a place of alighting or abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA: [but in the latter, in one place, said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosN","text_ar":"اـِنْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr; though a verse cited in both, as an ex., shows it to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anasN","text_ar":"اَنَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inhabitants of a house:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, TA:) pl. (of the word in the first sense, of these three, TA, and in the second, M, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=naAsN","text_ar":"ا=نَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One with whom a person is sociable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 136.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo A^anasu fulaAnK","text_ar":"هُمْ اَنَسُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are they with whom such a one is sociable"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aal~a*iyna yasotaA^onisu A_ilayohimo","text_ar":"اَلَّذِينَ يَسْتَاْنِسُ اـِلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (Lh, M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^anasu fulaAnK","text_ar":"هُوَ اَنَسُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is much accustomed to the serving of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 472.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","AA","TA"]}]}}